abstract: Fashion, an industry described as having the "shortest shelf life other than dairy and meat products," and cosmetics, the business of "achievable illusions," were the subjects of the first annual conference on Opportunities and Challenges held Saturday at the Fashion Institute of Technology.

abstract: Here is how Michael Crichton describes Amy, the principal love object in "Congo": "She could be coy, she responded to flattery, she was preoccupied with her appearance, loved makeup, and was very fussy about the collar of the sweaters she wore in the winter."

abstract: MARY HARRISON and Libby Dalton of Knoxville, Tenn., were sitting having a quiet drink in the oak-paneled lounge of the Algonquin Hotel Monday evening.  They knew that some pretty strange things happen in New York, but not until several people got down on their hands and knees in front of them, were they aware that the guest-of-honor at an adjoining party was underneath their chair.

WASHINGTON, Nov. 8--On Oct. 14, exactly three weeks before the election, Jimmy Carter's top political strategists assembled in Hamilton Jordan's Spartan campaign office to devise a plan to wiggle out of a debate with Ronald Reagan.
